## Versioning policy

{{project_name}} follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/):

- **MAJOR** — breaking API changes.
- **MINOR** — new features, backwards-compatible.
- **PATCH** — bug fixes, no API changes.

Pre-1.0: anything may change. Post-1.0: breaking changes require a major version bump.

---

## Release checklist (full)

Before tagging:

- [ ] CHANGELOG updated.
- [ ] VERSION bumped.
- [ ] All `make check` green.
- [ ] Documentation reflects the new release.
- [ ] Pre-1.0 → 1.0 transition: review the public API, mark anything not-stable as such.
- [ ] Built artifact installs cleanly in a fresh environment.

After tagging:

- [ ] `git push --tags`
- [ ] Published to package registry.
- [ ] GitHub Release prose written (paste from CHANGELOG section).
